    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Leonard B. Sand was an lawyer in New York State, and a delegate to the 1967 New York 
State Constitutional Convention.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Leonard B. Sand Papers</emph> consist of subject files relating to Sand's participation 
in the 1967 New York State Constitutional Convention.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Files are arranged alphabetically by subject.</p>
    </arrangement>
    <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
      <head>Related Material</head>
      <p>Additional 1967 Constitutional Convention material, including the Blaine Amendment, may be found in the <archref href="../c/corning_e2.htm">Erastus Corning II Papers</archref>.  
Other New York State Constitutional Conventions are represented in the papers of <archref href="../e/eastwood_a.htm">Asa Eastwood</archref> (1821), 
<archref href="../v/verplanck_gc.htm">Gulian C. Verplanck</archref> (1867, 1868), and <archref href="../c/corsi_e.htm">Edward Corsi</archref> (1938).</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
